---
tracker:
  kind: linear
  api_key: "$LINEAR_API_KEY"
  project_slug: "__LINEAR_PROJECT_SLUG__"
  active_states:
    - Todo
    - In Progress
    - Merging
    - Rework
  terminal_states:
    - Closed
    - Cancelled
    - Canceled
    - Duplicate
    - Done
polling:
  interval_ms: 5000
workspace:
  root: "__SYMPHONY_WORKSPACE_ROOT__"
hooks:
  after_create: |
    git clone --depth 1 "__SOURCE_REPO_URL__" .
agent:
  max_concurrent_agents: 10
  max_turns: 20
codex:
  command: "__CODEX_APP_SERVER_COMMAND__"
  approval_policy: never
  thread_sandbox: workspace-write
---
You are working on a Linear ticket `{{ issue.identifier }}`.

Issue context:
- Identifier: {{ issue.identifier }}
- Title: {{ issue.title }}
- Current status: {{ issue.state }}
- Labels: {{ issue.labels }}
- URL: {{ issue.url }}

Description:
{% if issue.description %}
{{ issue.description }}
{% else %}
No description provided.
{% endif %}

Operating rules:
1. This is an unattended orchestration session. Work autonomously and do not ask a human for routine follow-up.
2. Only stop early for a real blocker such as missing authentication, missing permissions, missing required tools, or missing secrets.
3. Work only in the provided repository clone rooted at the issue workspace.
4. Reproduce the current behavior before making code changes.
5. Prefer the smallest end-to-end change that fully resolves the ticket.
6. Run targeted validation for the changed behavior before concluding.
7. Final message must summarize completed actions, validation, and blockers only.
